WEBVTT

01:51.418 --> 01:53.084
How can I help you, sir?

01:54.751 --> 01:57.834
See the man talking to your
bank manager has his case open?

01:58.751 --> 02:01.209
That's Mr. Gwendon, one of
our assistant managers.

02:01.293 --> 02:03.584
Our manager is Mr. Schoen.
He's not in today.

02:03.709 --> 02:05.209
You see the man
with the briefcase?

02:05.293 --> 02:06.334
Yes.

02:06.418 --> 02:09.043
That's my partner.
He has a gun in there.

02:09.376 --> 02:12.001
If you don't do
exactly what I say,

02:12.084 --> 02:16.334
I'm gonna look at my partner and he'll
shoot Mr. Gwendon between the eyes.

02:17.251 --> 02:18.668
[SIGHS]

02:23.668 --> 02:28.709
Take one of those big envelopes and
pack it with 100s, 50s and 20s.

02:29.001 --> 02:33.001
Nothing with bank straps or rubber bands.
No dye packs. No bait money.

02:33.168 --> 02:36.584
Start with the second drawer,
then the one over there.

02:39.834 --> 02:43.293
It's okay. Come on, Loretta.
Key's right there next to you.

02:51.043 --> 02:53.751
No bills off the bottom
of the drawer, please.

03:00.751 --> 03:03.168
This your first time
being robbed?

03:03.876 --> 03:08.126
You're doing great. Just smile so you
don't look like you're being held up.

03:09.459 --> 03:11.334
You got a very pretty smile.

03:11.418 --> 03:13.709
Give me the 20s.
I'll take those.

03:14.418 --> 03:16.584
I'll put those in my pocket.

03:16.918 --> 03:18.376
There you go.

03:20.501 --> 03:23.126
I haven't had to signal my
partner, and that's good.

03:23.209 --> 03:27.168
He'll wait until I'll leave, to make
sure you don't set off the alarm.

03:27.584 --> 03:31.168
If you do, he'll shoot Mr.
Gwendon between the eyes.

03:33.543 --> 03:35.459
I think that'll do it, Loretta.

03:35.543 --> 03:37.584
Thank you. Have a nice day.

03:38.668 --> 03:39.918
You too.

03:47.709 --> 03:49.418
She's cute, isn't she?

03:50.334 --> 03:52.084
She seems very nice.

03:54.709 --> 03:56.168
Who was that?

04:22.626 --> 04:26.043
[IGNITION GRINDING]

04:28.334 --> 04:29.751
No, no, no.

04:29.834 --> 04:31.376
[PUMPING GAS PEDAL]

04:34.751 --> 04:35.793
Fuck!

04:37.418 --> 04:40.543
I think you flooded it.
Get out of the car, sir.

04:40.626 --> 04:41.751
[CHUCKLES]

04:42.668 --> 04:43.959
You wanna hear a funny story?

04:44.043 --> 04:46.251
Shut up and get out of the car!

04:46.834 --> 04:49.668
Yeah. Okay.

05:03.751 --> 05:07.001
[CHEERING]

05:19.418 --> 05:21.751
[APPLAUDING]

06:15.126 --> 06:16.334
[INAUDIBLE]

06:23.751 --> 06:25.834
You want something, Foley?

06:26.584 --> 06:29.876
Some fellas are going out of here.
Want to know where and when?

06:29.959 --> 06:31.043
How many?

06:31.126 --> 06:32.834
I expect you to look out for me.

06:33.334 --> 06:35.376
Okay. How many going out?

06:35.668 --> 06:37.543
- I hear six.
- When?

06:37.959 --> 06:39.834
Tonight.

06:39.918 --> 06:41.043
You know who they are?

06:41.251 --> 06:43.584
Yes, but I'm not
telling you yet.

06:44.126 --> 06:46.376
Meet me in the chapel
before lockdown.

06:55.876 --> 06:56.918
I love you, baby.

06:57.001 --> 06:59.459
Tonight's the big night.
You excited?

07:01.793 --> 07:04.293
It's Super Bowl Sunday, okay?

07:04.376 --> 07:05.418
You moved it up.

07:05.876 --> 07:07.168
Why do you think that?

07:07.251 --> 07:08.834
I saw you running this morning.

07:08.918 --> 07:10.918
Sticking to your routine,

07:11.668 --> 07:15.209
but you only did a couple of
miles, instead of your usual five.

07:15.293 --> 07:17.084
Saving yourself
for the big event.

07:17.168 --> 07:19.126
What happened? Finished early?

07:19.209 --> 07:21.459
You see those posts out there?

07:21.918 --> 07:23.501
They're putting up another fence

07:23.584 --> 07:26.584
15 feet back the fence
that's already there.

07:26.959 --> 07:30.543
So if on Super Bowl Sunday,
they have that fence built

07:31.043 --> 07:34.209
then we have to dig, what,
another nine, ten days?

07:34.418 --> 07:35.751
I don't think so.

07:35.834 --> 07:40.251
So tonight, when it's dark, I'm
out of here. You can come, Foley.

07:41.251 --> 07:44.001
I appreciate the offer,
and it's tempting,

07:45.168 --> 07:47.918
but it's a long run,
a hundred miles to Miami?

07:48.126 --> 07:50.959
I'm too old to be
trying a stunt like that.

07:52.334 --> 07:53.793
Send me a postcard
when you get out.

07:57.209 --> 07:58.209
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

08:06.459 --> 08:08.251
Adele Delisi speaking.

08:08.334 --> 08:11.418
OPERATOR: <i>Will you accept</i> a
<i>collect call from Jack Foley?</i>

08:12.584 --> 08:13.918
I'll accept.

08:14.334 --> 08:15.626
Adele, how you doing?

08:15.709 --> 08:17.084
Hey, bank robber.

08:17.876 --> 08:21.209
Want some advice? Next time,
keep the engine running.

08:22.251 --> 08:23.876
That's funny!

08:23.959 --> 08:25.084
What do you want?

08:27.126 --> 08:30.751
That Super Bowl party
that was for next Sunday,

08:31.209 --> 08:33.418
it's tonight at 6:30.

08:34.251 --> 08:36.583
You said one-time calls
aren't monitored.

08:36.668 --> 08:37.918
<i>Not as a rule.</i>

08:38.293 --> 08:41.043
So why don't you just tell me
what you're talking about.

08:41.126 --> 08:43.251
Miss Smarty Mouth,
in the free world.

08:43.333 --> 08:44.751
<i>What's free about it?</i>

08:45.751 --> 08:47.126
I'm lookin' for work.

08:47.251 --> 08:49.043
What about
Mandrake the Magician?

08:49.126 --> 08:50.918
<i>Emile the Amazing.</i>

08:52.459 --> 08:55.418
He fired me. Hired a younger girl.
A redhead.

08:56.084 --> 08:58.918
I'm calling because
they changed the date.

08:59.376 --> 09:02.418
It's tonight at 6:30,
a few hours from now.

09:02.501 --> 09:04.293
<i>You tell Buddy.</i>

09:04.376 --> 09:05.751
And the guy driving
the other car?

09:06.001 --> 09:07.668
What guy?

09:07.751 --> 09:09.251
As you have so
much luck with cars,

09:10.251 --> 09:12.709
Buddy thought it might
be better to bring two.

09:12.793 --> 09:15.168
He got a guy he says
you know from Lompoc.

09:15.251 --> 09:16.501
<i>Glenn somebody.</i>

09:16.584 --> 09:17.584
Glenn Michaels.

09:18.001 --> 09:22.251
Uh-huh. That's him. Buddy said Glenn
thinks you guys are real cool.

09:24.376 --> 09:28.084
Tell Buddy if Glenn's wearing
sunglasses, I'll step on them.

09:28.334 --> 09:30.043
I might not even
take them off first.

09:30.126 --> 09:31.418
I'll sure do that.

09:31.501 --> 09:34.001
Okay, hon. Now, try
not to get shot. Bye.

09:57.459 --> 09:59.126
Ma'am. Let me help you.

09:59.209 --> 10:02.251
A lady like you shouldn't
be carrying groceries.

10:02.334 --> 10:04.334
Let a man do that for you.

10:08.001 --> 10:11.168
I didn't ask for your help,
so don't expect a tip.

10:12.043 --> 10:15.376
That's okay, Ma'am.
I'll just take your car.

10:17.959 --> 10:19.293
MARSHALL: Happy birthday.

10:19.376 --> 10:21.251
Did you fit another
Chanel suit in here?

10:21.334 --> 10:23.501
Something much better. Open it.

10:30.959 --> 10:33.043
Oh, my God. It's beautiful.

10:34.959 --> 10:36.043
It's a...

10:36.126 --> 10:37.168
<i>SIG Sauer 380.</i>

10:37.251 --> 10:38.959
Right.

10:39.043 --> 10:40.084
I love it!

10:42.126 --> 10:43.501
Thanks, Dad.

10:43.918 --> 10:45.459
Happy birthday.

10:46.126 --> 10:48.084
Some more coffee? I can't.

10:48.334 --> 10:52.709
I have to go out to Glades, then
I'm meeting Ray Nicolet at 10:00.

10:52.793 --> 10:55.376
Which one is that?
The A.T.F. guy?

10:55.751 --> 10:58.626
He's with the F.B.I. now.
He switched over.

10:59.418 --> 11:01.334
He's still married, though.

11:01.418 --> 11:03.376
Technically. They're separated.

11:03.793 --> 11:04.834
He moved out then?

11:04.918 --> 11:05.959
He's about to.

11:06.751 --> 11:08.293
Then they're not separated.

11:08.376 --> 11:10.334
Can we not talk about this?

11:12.251 --> 11:13.334
What are you doing at Glades?

11:13.376 --> 11:15.918
Serving a summons and complaint.

11:16.126 --> 11:19.043
Some con doing life doesn't
like macaroni and cheese.

11:19.126 --> 11:23.709
So, he files suit, says he has
no choice on what they serve,

11:23.793 --> 11:26.126
which violates his civil rights.

11:26.251 --> 11:30.084
You can step in, work for me
as one of my investigators.

11:31.043 --> 11:32.043
No, thanks.

11:32.084 --> 11:33.126
You used to like it.

11:34.584 --> 11:38.709
You'd meet doctors, lawyers. They're
all fine, if they're divorced.

11:39.459 --> 11:43.501
Karen, why waste your time
on some cowboy cop

11:43.584 --> 11:45.501
who drinks and
cheats on his wife?

11:45.584 --> 11:47.918
That's how those hot shots are.

11:48.251 --> 11:49.918
I really gotta go.

11:54.084 --> 11:56.126
We don't talk much anymore.

11:58.918 --> 12:02.918
How about I come over Sunday and
we watch the Super Bowl together?

12:03.418 --> 12:04.918
I'd like that.

12:06.418 --> 12:08.251
Thanks for the gun, Dad.

12:23.084 --> 12:25.501
They dug a tunnel
underneath you.

12:25.709 --> 12:29.459
I don't hear anything.
Where's the tunnel come out?

12:31.543 --> 12:33.876
Fourth post from
the guard tower.

12:34.251 --> 12:36.043
I don't see nothing.

12:36.876 --> 12:38.584
Just keep watching.

12:57.126 --> 12:58.126
[DIALING]

13:00.584 --> 13:02.959
<i>OPERATOR: F.B.I.</i>
<i>How may I direct your call?</i>

13:03.334 --> 13:05.876
This is Karen Sisco
again for Ray Nicolet.

13:05.959 --> 13:07.459
<i>Hold, please.</i>

13:08.043 --> 13:09.084
Yeah.

13:31.668 --> 13:33.918
<i>The line is busy.</i>
<i>You want his voice mail?</i>

13:34.001 --> 13:36.626
No, forget it.
I'll call back later.

13:36.793 --> 13:38.543
<i>All right. Thanks.</i>

13:40.001 --> 13:41.959
I still don't see anything.

13:43.709 --> 13:45.376
You will directly.

13:48.959 --> 13:50.459
OFFICER: Wait a minute!

14:00.584 --> 14:02.626
[DIGGING]

14:12.251 --> 14:13.751
What the fuck?

14:20.751 --> 14:23.793
[HONKING]

14:28.584 --> 14:30.376
Two men by the fence!

14:32.751 --> 14:34.626
[SIRENS WAILING]

14:34.709 --> 14:36.918
[MACHINE GUN FIRING]

14:48.251 --> 14:50.418
What the hell is she doing?

15:00.251 --> 15:01.751
Stop! Get your hands in the air!

15:06.709 --> 15:09.751
[GUARDS SHOUTING]

15:19.876 --> 15:21.168
Tunnel's clear.

15:22.084 --> 15:23.168
Seal up the north face.

15:23.251 --> 15:24.584
GUARD: What happened?

15:24.668 --> 15:26.584
What do you think?
Got a jail break!

15:27.084 --> 15:28.834
The Cubans are out in the cane.

15:28.918 --> 15:30.668
Don't point that at me.
Hey, Buddy.

15:30.751 --> 15:31.959
It's okay, we're the good guys.

15:32.043 --> 15:33.376
What are you doing here?

15:36.418 --> 15:38.751
You're just a girl.
Why the shotgun?

15:38.834 --> 15:40.543
I'm a federal marshal.
You're under arrest.

15:43.626 --> 15:46.001
Why don't we talk
about this later?

15:47.626 --> 15:48.793
Watch your head.

15:49.709 --> 15:50.918
I'm in. Let's go!

15:53.918 --> 15:55.751
JACK: You comfy?

15:55.834 --> 15:57.126
If I could have
a little more room...

15:57.168 --> 15:58.834
Well, there isn't any.

15:59.293 --> 16:02.126
There's a lot of shit in here.
Handcuffs.

16:02.668 --> 16:04.418
What's in this can?

16:05.126 --> 16:08.168
That's for your breath.
Squirt some in your mouth.

16:08.418 --> 16:10.293
That's Mace, isn't it?

16:10.918 --> 16:11.918
[MEN SHOUTING]

16:23.709 --> 16:25.418
Where's your gun? Your pistol?

16:27.043 --> 16:28.251
In my bag, in the car.

16:39.418 --> 16:40.918
Boy, it stunk in there.

16:41.584 --> 16:44.709
I believe it. You're ruining
a $900 suit my dad gave me.

16:44.793 --> 16:47.168
It went great
with that 12-gauge.

16:47.251 --> 16:49.959
Why would someone like you
become a marshal?

16:50.043 --> 16:51.709
To go after guys like you.

16:51.793 --> 16:52.834
What was that?

16:52.918 --> 16:55.043
Guys like me?
Let me tell you something.

16:55.126 --> 16:56.834
Even though I've been
celibate lately,

16:56.918 --> 16:58.543
I'm not forcing myself on you.

16:58.626 --> 16:59.834
I've never done that.

16:59.918 --> 17:01.084
You won't have time.

17:01.168 --> 17:02.751
We hit a roadblock,
they run the car

17:02.834 --> 17:04.542
and find out who it belongs to.

17:04.626 --> 17:07.917
I doubt they'll get one set up in time.
If they do,

17:08.001 --> 17:11.792
they'll be lookin' for two Latin
fellas, not a big black guy.

17:12.501 --> 17:15.417
<i>KAREN: He must be quite a pal,</i>
<i>to risk his own ass like this.</i>

17:15.501 --> 17:17.209
<i>JACK: Buddy? He's a good guy.</i>

17:17.292 --> 17:18.584
<i>When we jailed together,</i>

17:18.667 --> 17:21.376
<i>he would call his sister</i>
<i>every week, without fail.</i>

17:21.459 --> 17:25.584
<i>She's a born-again Christian. She</i>
<i>does bookkeeping for a televangelist.</i>

17:25.667 --> 17:27.542
<i>He'd call her up,</i>
<i>confess his sins.</i>

17:27.626 --> 17:29.918
<i>Tell her whatever</i>
<i>bank he'd robbed.</i>

17:31.251 --> 17:32.793
<i>KAREN: Buddy, that his given name?</i>

17:32.876 --> 17:34.876
<i>JACK: The one I gave him, yeah.</i>

17:35.376 --> 17:37.001
<i>KAREN: What's your name?</i>

17:38.709 --> 17:41.084
<i>It'll be in the paper</i>
<i>tomorrow anyway.</i>

17:41.251 --> 17:43.959
Jack Foley. You've
probably heard of me.

17:44.376 --> 17:46.043
Why? Are you famous?

17:46.126 --> 17:47.793
The time I was
convicted in California,

17:47.876 --> 17:51.918
the F.B.I. told me that I'd robbed more
banks than anybody in the computer.

17:52.751 --> 17:53.876
How many was that?

17:53.959 --> 17:55.418
I don't really know.

17:56.459 --> 17:58.543
I started when I was 18,

17:58.626 --> 18:00.668
I drove for my uncle Cully,
and his partner, Gus.

18:01.459 --> 18:04.668
Basically you're saying you
spent half your life in prison.

18:04.751 --> 18:08.084
Basically, yeah. If I
go back, I do 30 years.

18:08.418 --> 18:10.001
You imagine looking at that?

18:10.084 --> 18:11.626
I don't have to.
I don't rob banks.

18:16.084 --> 18:18.418
<i>JACK: You don't</i>
<i>seem all that scared.</i>

18:19.084 --> 18:20.084
Of course I am.

18:20.126 --> 18:21.751
You don't act like it.

18:22.168 --> 18:24.126
Do you want me to scream?

18:24.334 --> 18:26.418
That wouldn't help much anyway.

18:26.751 --> 18:29.584
I'm just gonna sit here,
take it easy,

18:29.668 --> 18:30.834
and wait for you to screw up.

18:30.876 --> 18:31.876
[JACK CHUCKLES]

18:31.959 --> 18:34.001
JACK: You sound like my ex-wife.

18:34.168 --> 18:35.668
You were married?

18:35.751 --> 18:37.834
For about a year,
give or take a few days.

18:38.626 --> 18:41.543
It's not like we didn't get along.
We had fun. We just

18:41.626 --> 18:44.251
didn't have that thing,
you know,

18:45.293 --> 18:47.501
that spark. Gotta have that.

18:48.959 --> 18:50.001
Uh-huh.

18:50.084 --> 18:51.168
We still talk, though.

18:51.251 --> 18:52.251
Sure.

18:55.334 --> 18:57.751
KAREN: This is not gonna end well.
These things never do.

18:58.418 --> 19:00.959
If I'm going to get shot
it's gonna be in the street,

19:01.043 --> 19:02.959
not off a goddamn fence.

19:03.251 --> 19:06.918
You must really see yourself
as some kind of Clyde Barrow.

19:11.709 --> 19:13.709
You mean, of "Bonnie and Clyde"?

19:18.084 --> 19:21.918
The part of the movie where they
get shot, Warren Beatty and

19:22.918 --> 19:24.376
Faye Dunaway.

19:24.459 --> 19:27.043
I like her in
that movie about TV.

19:27.126 --> 19:28.376
<i>Network. She was</i> good.

19:28.751 --> 19:31.709
That guy who says he won't
take any more shit.

19:31.876 --> 19:33.251
Peter Finch.

19:35.876 --> 19:39.418
"I'm mad as hell, and I'm not gonna
take any more of your shit!"

19:41.084 --> 19:44.001
In the part where they
get shot, I remember

19:44.084 --> 19:47.876
thinking that it wouldn't be such
a bad way to go, if you had to.

19:51.043 --> 19:53.001
[SIRENS WAILING]

20:09.209 --> 20:11.418
JACK: You sure
are easy to talk to.

20:15.084 --> 20:18.668
I was thinking, if we met under
different circumstances,

20:19.793 --> 20:23.251
if you were in a bar and I came
up and we started talking,

20:24.334 --> 20:26.168
I wonder what would happen.
Nothing.

20:26.251 --> 20:27.626
If you didn't know who I was.

20:27.709 --> 20:29.084
You'd probably tell me.

20:29.168 --> 20:31.043
But if circumstances
were different...

20:31.126 --> 20:32.959
You have got to be kidding.

20:35.918 --> 20:40.001
Another Faye Dunaway movie I liked
was <i>Three Days of</i> the Condor.

20:41.251 --> 20:43.918
The one with Robert Redford
when he was young.

20:47.334 --> 20:49.668
I never thought
it made sense though.

20:50.501 --> 20:53.001
The way they got
together so quick.

20:53.459 --> 20:54.668
Really?

20:55.668 --> 20:57.459
I mean, romantically.

21:04.876 --> 21:07.376
JACK: Here we go.
Where the hell are we?

21:07.834 --> 21:10.209
BUDDY: Turnpike. Glenn's
above us with the other car.

21:10.293 --> 21:11.668
JACK: Hop on out.

21:11.751 --> 21:13.084
Turn around and
get your hands up!

21:13.334 --> 21:14.709
[GUNSHOTS FIRING]

21:14.793 --> 21:16.918
BUDDY: We may as well leave her.
We're leavin' the car

21:16.959 --> 21:18.918
and we gotta
leave her some place.

21:19.001 --> 21:20.084
She's coming with us.

21:20.668 --> 21:22.168
Jesus, what were
you doing in there?

21:23.126 --> 21:24.876
Looking for a name.
I already looked.

21:24.959 --> 21:28.459
Her name is Karen Sisco. Like the
Cisco Kid, only spelled different.

21:32.084 --> 21:33.084
[SIRENS WAILING]

21:38.251 --> 21:40.293
Karen? You be a good girl now.

21:40.418 --> 21:42.418
I'm gonna open up the trunk.

21:42.501 --> 21:45.626
Hey! You're putting holes
in your car!

21:46.959 --> 21:52.001
I'm not leavin' you. I'll open the trunk.
Drop your pistol out.

21:52.626 --> 21:56.751
If you shoot, Buddy's got your shotgun.
He'll shoot back.

21:57.126 --> 21:59.751
I can't stop him.
So it's up to you.

21:59.876 --> 22:00.876
GLENN: Hew.

22:02.084 --> 22:03.501
Don't! It's Glenn!

22:04.418 --> 22:07.793
Fuck! Jack. Good to see you.

22:07.876 --> 22:10.084
What are you guys shooting at?

22:11.418 --> 22:12.459
Do we need him?

22:12.543 --> 22:13.543
The cop saw this car.

22:13.626 --> 22:16.501
He might tie it to the break
and turn around.

22:16.584 --> 22:18.751
Hey, Studs.
We didn't recognize you.

22:18.834 --> 22:20.251
Hey, "Studs."

22:21.751 --> 22:26.293
I haven't heard that since Lompoc.
What's going on?

22:28.084 --> 22:29.293
Nothing.

22:30.626 --> 22:34.584
Karen. Are you coming out?

22:37.043 --> 22:38.043
[COCKING]

22:38.126 --> 22:39.918
You hear that? Okay.

22:52.751 --> 22:54.251
You win, Jack.

